## Rust FFI in R

#### 1.Write Rust Code

```rust
#[no_mangle]    //tell interpter not to change func name
pub fn dbl(n: i32) -> i32{
   n*2
}
```

#### 2.Generate DLL file

in cmd , we could use function as follows:

```bash
rustc --crate-type dylib dbl.rs
```

- ruslt

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

#### 3.Write Cpp Warpper

```cpp
//embed.cpp

extern "C" {
    int dbl(int);
}

// [[Rcpp::export]]
int cpp_dbl(int k) {
  int f = dbl(k);
  return(f);
}
```

#### 4.Specifying System Env and generate R Function

```R
library(Rcpp)
Sys.setenv("PKG_LIBS"="-L D:/Code/test -l hello")
## param "-L" specifies lib folder
## param "-l" specifies lib name

sourceCpp("embed.cpp", verbose = T, rebuild = T)
## generating R function
```
